	A large dream catcher with a wonderful image titled &lsquo;Wolf Trio&rsquo; featuring three wolves in a snow covered forest. Dream catchers are based on the Native American tradition of hanging a symbolic web over a sleeping person to protect him or her from bad dreams. Hung above the dreamer, the dream catcher filters dreams from the night air, letting only the good dreams or important messages through into the feathers and then down onto the person sleeping and catching all bad dreams within the web. Very popular with children suffering bad dreams these wolf designs are now our best sellers. This dream catcher is approx. 80cm long from the hook to the bottom feather and the actual picture has a diameter of approximately 32cm. Click on the title above to see the full dream catcher.</p>
